{"title": "Permissive origin in postMessage", "summary": "  Using \"*\" (any) as the target origin of a postMessage call allows third-parties to read the message. ", "description": "\n\nUsing \"*\" (any) as the target origin of a postMessage call allows\nthird-parties to read the message.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid using \"*\" as the target origin:\n\n```javascript\nwindow.postMessage(message, '*')\n```\n\n\u2705 Specify the origin for your target application:\n\n```javascript\nwindow.postMessage(message, 'https://myapp.example.com')\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-346"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/javascript_lang_post_message_origin"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}